        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 21 at 2:00AM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 200 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Gilmer, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gilmer, Daingerfield, Hughes Springs, Lone Star, Ore City, Cedar
Springs, Jenkins, Midway, Lafayette, Holly Springs, Center Point
and Bettie.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
